      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a draft of the rejection email:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the Senior Developer position at our company in Austin. We were impressed by your impressive technical skills and outstanding performance throughout our interview process. However, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our specific cloud architecture needs.\n\nWhile this decision was not made lightly, we believe it is in the best interest of the company. Please know that we were particularly drawn to your strong work ethic and passion for coding, and we appreciate the time you took to interview with us. We wish you the very best in your future endeavors and hope our paths will cross again soon.\n\nBest regards, [Your Name]",
