      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks, that's a good start. It's a bit formal though. Could you try to make it sound a little more \"human\" and warm? Like, maybe add a sentence or two that acknowledges the difficulty of the choice we had to make, so it doesn't feel like a template? Just keep it professional, obviously, but not so cold.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a revised draft:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the Senior Developer position at our company in Austin. We were truly impressed by your impressive technical skills and outstanding performance throughout our interview process. You brought a level of enthusiasm and expertise that was evident in everything you did, and we were heartened to see a candidate who shares our passion for innovation and collaboration.\n\nI want to start by saying that this decision was by no means easy for us – we were all charmed by your energy and impressed by your accomplishments. However, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our specific cloud architecture needs. Please know that we were particularly drawn to your strong work ethic and passion for coding, and we appreciate the time you took to interview with us.\n\nWe wish you the very best in your future endeavors and hope our paths will cross again soon. Thank you again for the opportunity to meet you and learn more about your skills and experience.\n\nBest regards, [Your Name]\n\nThis version aims to convey a warmer tone while still being professional, and acknowledges the difficulty of the decision.",
